         <abstract>
            <p>We prove that there is no positive measure d σ on (a, b) such that the corresponding Gauss-Kronrod quadrature formula is also a Chebyshev quadrature formula. The same is true if we consider measures of the form dσ (t) = ω(t)dt, where ω(t) is even, on a symmetric interval (-a, a), and the Gauss-Kronrod formula is required to have equal weights only for n even. We also show that the only positive and even measure d σ(t) = d σ(-t) on (-1, 1) for which the Gauss-Kronrod formula has all weights equal if n = 1, or has the form ∫&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;-1&lt;/sub&gt;f(t)d σ(t) = w ∑&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;v = 1&lt;/sub&gt; f(τ&lt;sub&gt;ν&lt;/sub&gt;) + w&lt;sub&gt;1f&lt;/sub&gt;(1) + w ∑&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;μ = 2&lt;/sub&gt; f(τ&lt;sup&gt;*&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;μ&lt;/sub&gt;) + w&lt;sub&gt;1f&lt;/sub&gt;(-1) + R&lt;sup&gt;K&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(f) for all n ≥ 2, is the Chebyshev measure of the first kind d σ&lt;sub&gt;C&lt;/sub&gt;(t) = (1 - t&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)&lt;sup&gt;-1/2&lt;/sup&gt;dt.</p>
          </abstract>
